summary.purpose: Barrel file that aggregates and re-exports all enum definitions from the enums sub-module.
summary.problem_solved: Provides a single import point for all enumerations so consumers do not need to know which specific file within enums/ defines each enum.

internal.why_used: Re-exports global domain enums: DefaultClient, BoardStatus, EquipmentStatus, EquipmentStatusReason, UnitStatus, ClientStatus, LanguageOptions, CountryOptions, SiteType
Re-exports RuptelaEventEnum for Ruptela GPS device event identification
Re-exports all feature-flag enums and user permission types: FeaturesBoard, FeaturesClient, FeaturesDashboard, FeaturesInstaller, FeaturesToolbox, UserPermissionsObject, userPermissionsObjectValue

exports.name: features (re-export)
exports.description_one_line: Re-exports all feature-flag enums and permission types

symbols.name: global (re-export)
symbols.description_one_line: Barrel re-export of all global domain enums from enums/global.ts

details.what_it_does: Makes DefaultClient, BoardStatus, EquipmentStatus, EquipmentStatusReason, UnitStatus, ClientStatus, LanguageOptions, CountryOptions, and SiteType available through the enums barrel.

minimal_correct.title: Import a global enum via the enums barrel
minimal_correct.code:
import { ClientStatus } from 'akeyless-types-commons';
// ClientStatus is available because enums/index.ts re-exports enums/global.ts
